                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding calendar="Gregorian" notBefore="1600" notAfter="1700">
                        <p> Standard Merton s. xvii, sewn on six bands; formerly chained from
               the usual position. Near the foot of f. 342 are the marks of the large iron
               chain-staple. Marks on f. i suggest a central strap replaced by two, on a previous
               binding, and perhaps an iron chain-staple at the foot. The outermost leaves were
               pastedowns in an earlier binding. </p>
